--0.9_5.
[Bugfixes]
 [Bug] [color=orange]if for some reason (server crashing etc.) no full server save was executed, it is likely that the galaxytick.txt file was never created and therefore the calculation couldn't be done properly which might feel like the mod is not working.[/color]
if you see the following on every serverstart in your serverlog:

[code]
Wed Feb 08 00:40:38 2017| [OOSP] This is not critical on first start:
Wed Feb 08 00:40:38 2017|  Loading galaxyticks failed: data/scripts/server/tickhandler.lua:34: cannot open file 'galaxyticks.txt' (No such file or directory)[/code]

[list]
[li]Chances are very high you suffer from this problem.
Only if you show these symptoms place this in data/scripts/server:
[s]https://www.dropbox.com/s/pmzol06p4b1n291/tickhandler.lua?dl=1[/s][/li]
[li][color=green]a bug where the ticks weren't saved on the server[/color][/li]
[li][color=green]a bug where removing/taking ressources within in the update process crashed and stopped working for that exact Player[/color] (not serverwide)[/li]
[li][color=green] resolved incompatibility with shipyard.lua[/color][/li]
[li][color=green]jumping with multiple Asteroids at the same time caused a servercrash[/color].- This one was hard to fix.[/li]
[/list]

